24120%20billion%20fortune%20ranks%20him%20sixth%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fbillionaires%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%20Billionaire%20Index%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He's%20an%20anomaly%20among%20the%20top%2010%20men%2C%20who%20either%20started%20their%20flagship%20companies%20(Bill%20Gates%2C%20Jeff%20Bezos%2C%20Larry%20Ellison%2C%20Zuckerberg%2C%20Brin%2C%20and%20Page)%20or%20still%20run%20them%20today%20(Elon%20Musk%2C%20Bernard%20Arnault%2C%20Buffett.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20retired%20Microsoft%20chief%20is%20many%20times%20richer%20than%20most%20corporate%20executives%20because%20of%20his%20original%20contract%20with%20the%20software%20giant.%20When%20he%20joined%20as%20its%2030th%20employee%20in%201980%2C%20he%20negotiated%20a%20%2450%2C000%20base%20salary%20plus%2010%25%20of%20the%20profit%20growth%20he%20could%20generate%20as%20his%20compensation%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fgeorgeanders%2F2014%2F09%2F30%2Flong-ago-twist-yielded-ballmer-a-fortune-in-microsoft-stock%2F%3Fsh%3D70f78eb336a5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Forbes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBallmer's%20cut%20of%20the%20profits%20eventually%20became%20excessive%2C%20so%20he%20agreed%20to%20give%20it%20up%20in%20exchange%20for%20a%20sizeable%20equity%20stake.%20He%20served%20as%20Microsoft's%20CEO%20from%202000%20until%202014%2C%20when%20he%20retired%20with%20333%20million%20shares%20or%204%25%20ownership%20of%20the%20company%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2FArchives%2Fedgar%2Fdata%2F789019%2F000119312514376415%2Fd694241ddef14a.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregulatory%20filings%20show%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBloomberg%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fbillionaires%2Fprofiles%2Fsteve-a-ballmer%2F%3Fin_source%3Dembedded-checkout-banner%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestimates%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Ballmer%20still%20owns%20a%20similar%20stake%20today%20%E2%80%94%20a%20position%20worth%20over%20%24100%20billion%20based%20on%20Microsoft's%20current%20market%20capitalization%20of%20%242.6%20trillion.%20The%20LA%20Clippers%20owner%20has%20likely%20collected%20more%20than%20%2412%20billion%20of%20dividends%20over%20time%20as%20well%2C%20the%20news%20outlet%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBallmer%20has%20benefited%20from%20the%20buzz%20around%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20which%20Microsoft%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-investing-billions-into-chatgpt-creator-openai-partnership-2023-1%5C%22%3Etapped%20into%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20it%20plowed%20%2410%20billion%20into%20ChatGPT-parent%20OpenAI%20earlier%20this%20spring.%20The%20tech%20titan's%20stock%20has%20soared%2044%25%20this%20year%2C%20and%20hit%20a%20record%20high%20last%20week.%20The%20surge%20has%20fueled%20a%20%2434%20billion%20rise%20in%20Ballmer's%20net%20worth%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBerkshire%20Hathaway%20stock%20is%20also%20trading%20close%20to%20an%20all-time%20high%2C%20but%20Buffett%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwarren-buffett-philanthropy-gates-foundation-berkshire-hathaway-stock-shares-gifts-2023-6%5C%22%3Egifted%20over%20half%20of%20his%20shares%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20and%20four%20family%20foundations.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20investor%20and%20Berkshire%20CEO's%20fortune%20stands%20at%20%24118%20billion%20%E2%80%94%20he%20would%20likely%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwarren-buffett-berkshire-hathaway-elon-musk-tesla-stock-wealth-philanthropy-2022-1%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWarren%2520Buffett%2520would%2520be%2520richer%2520than%2520Elon%2520Musk%2520if%2520he%2Cstock%2520worth%2520%2524111%2520billion%2520today%26amp%3Btext%3DWarren%2520Buffett%2527s%2520net