%20work%20early%20in%20the%20pandemic%20allowed%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F06%2F28%2Fnyregion%2Fwealthy-pandemic-nyc.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewealthy%20residents%20to%20ditch%20big%20cities%20in%20droves%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20set%20up%20shop%20in%20smaller%20cities%20and%20towns%20nearby.%20This%20mass%20reshuffling%20caused%20huge%20spikes%20and%20dips%20in%20populations%2C%20and%20nearly%20every%20locale%20across%20the%20country%20has%20felt%20the%20impact%20at%20some%20point.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20Hudson%20Valley%20%E2%80%94%20the%20constellation%20of%20small%20cities%20and%20towns%20north%20of%20New%20York%20City%20%E2%80%94%20saw%20a%20massive%20influx%20in%202021%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.realestateindepth.com%2Fnews%2Fpattern-study-confirms-nyc-migration-to-hudson-valley%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eover%2030%2C000%20residents%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20ditched%20their%20Manhattan%20apartments%20for%20farmhouses.%20Midsize%20cities%20across%20the%20US%20like%20Austin%2C%20Texas%20and%20Charlotte%2C%20North%20Carolina%20have%20seen%20a%20similar%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzoom-town-inequality-remote-workers-work-from-home-big-cities-2022-4%5C%22%3Eboom%20in%20newcomers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Now%20that%20the%20dust%20is%20settling%2C%20increased%20rents%20and%20the%20stickiness%20of%20working%20from%20home%20have%20pushed%20small%20and%20midsize%20cities%20to%20adjust%20to%20a%20new%20normal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20surging%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-workers-moving-to-zoomtowns-southwest-cities-drought-no-water-2022-10%5C%22%3Ecosts%20of%20housing%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20new%20freedom%20of%20remote%20work%20helped%20trigger%20this%20mass%20migration%2C%20small%20cities%20have%20been%20laying%20the%20groundwork%20over%20the%20last%20decade%20to%20entice%20these%20big-city%20refugees.%20The%20new%20playbook%20for%20up-and-coming%20metros%2C%20which%20I%20detailed%20in%20my%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20City%20Authentic%3A%20How%20the%20Attention%20Economic%20Builds%20Urban%20America%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20to%20engineer%20the%20entire%20city%20to%20produce%20the%20kind%20of%20amenities%20that%20middle-%20and%20high-income%20workers%20have%20come%20to%20expect%20from%20an%20urban%20neighborhood%20%E2%80%94%20walkable%20downtowns%2C%20diverse%20restaurants%2C%20craft-brew%20pubs%20%E2%80%94%20at%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20price.%20These%20cities%20want%20to%20convince%20potential%20transplants%20that%20they%20%3Cem%3Ecan%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehave%20it%20all.%20%26quot%3BTo%20a%20growing%20degree%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2023%2F05%2F15%2Fupshot%2Fmigrations-college-super-cities.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20recently%20reported%20about%20those%20leaving%20large%20metros%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20they%20left%20behind%20they%20can%20find%20in%20Charlotte%2C%20Denver%2C%20Minneapolis%2C%20Salt%20Lake%20City%2C%20Dallas%20or%20Louisville.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20these%20urban-renewal%20projects%20come%20with%20a%20dark%20side.%20Sure%2C%20they%20have%20been%20successful%20in%20attracting%20young%20professionals%20to%20what%20were%20once%20considered%20second-%20or%20third-tier%20cities%2C%20but%20they%20have%20also%20turned%20cities%20across%20the%20US%20into%20replicas%20of%20each%20other.%20In%20their%20attempts%20to%20stand%20out%2C%20many%20places%20have%20started%20to%20look%20exactly%20the%20same.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20fight%20over%20the%20creative%20class%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20people%20don't%20think%20of%20the%201988%20Tim%20Burton%20film%20%26quot%3BBeetlejuice%26quot%3B%20as%20a%20tale%20about%20urban%20development.%20But%20the%20Deetzes%2C%20a%20family%20who%20moves%20into%20a%20newly-haunted%20house%2C%20are%20a%20classic%201980s%20striver%20couple%20%E2%80%94%20a%20real-estate%20agent%20and%20a%20self-described%20artist%20%E2%80%94%20who%20can't%20help%20but%20transform%20everything%20in%20their%20sleepy%20Connecticut%20town%20into%20some%20sort%20of%20consumable%20experience%20for%20city%20folk%20just%20like%20them.%20While%20perhaps%20a%20bit%20overdone%2C%20the%20Deetzes%20are%20the%20perfect%20pop-culture%20example%20of%20the%20type%20of%20people%20cities%20have%20been%20trying%20to%20attract%20for%20the%20past%2040%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20America's%20manufacturing%20jobs%20shifted%20abroad%20and%20city%20governments%20cut%20back%20on%20investment%20in%20the%201980s%20and%201990s%2C%20the%20finance%2C%20insurance%2C%20and%20real-estate%20industries%20emerged%20as%20the%20biggest%20business%20concerns%20in%20urban%20America.%20Unlike%20factory%20work%2C%20these%20businesses%20employed%20fewer%2C%20better-paid%2C%20white-collar%20office%20workers%20who%20had%20much%20more%20flexibility%20in%20where%20and%20when%20they%20worked.%20This%20burgeoning%20%26quot%3Bcreative%20class%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20urban-studies%20theorist%20and%20professor%20Richard%20Florida%20called%20them%20in%20his%202002%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Rise%20of%20the%20Creative%20Class%2C%26quot%3B%20was%20composed%20of%20graphic%20designers%2C%20web%20developers%2C%20and%20marketing%20professionals.%20The%20most%20creative%20and%20economically%20successful%20cities%2C%20Florida%20argued%2C%20were%20ones%20that%20catered%20to%20the%20lifestyles%20of%20these%20highly%20mobile%20professionals.%20In%20response%2C%20cities%20across%20the%20globe%20sought%20to%20establish%20cosmopolitan%20downtowns%20that%20would%20be%20welcoming%20to%20upper-class%20creatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmaller%20cities%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20struggled%20to%20attract%20good%20employers%20and%20develop%20successful%20entrepreneurs.%20In%202017%2C%20Florida%20wrote%20%26quot%3BThe%20New%20Urban%20Crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20admitted%20that%20the%20approach%20he%20spearheaded%20had%20significantly%20contributed%20to%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F27119057%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewinner-take-all%20urbanism%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%3A%20Big%20cities%20grew%2C%20but%20small%20and%20medium%20cities%20withered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20came%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20remote%20work%20suddenly%20made%20small%20cities%20a%20viable%20home%20for%20wealthy%20professionals.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2023%2F05%2F15%2Fupshot%2Fmigrations-college-super-cities.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20%3C%2Fa%3Ereported%20in%20May%20that%20the%20middle%20class%20was%20being%20priced%20out%20of%20big%20cities%2C%20which%2C%20collectively%2C%20lost%20over%20200%2C000%20people%20in%202021.%20After%20a%2040-year%20march%20to%20a%20few%20major%20urban%20centers%2C%20the%20eyes%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bcreative%20class%26quot%3B%20began%20to%20wander%20across%20the%20map.%20Many%20workers%20relocated%20to%20cities%20of%20less%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20a%20million%20people%2C%20a%20class%20of%20city%20that%20hasn't%20seen%20a%20net%20increase%20in%20population%20in%20over%20a%20decade.%20But%20the%20cities%20that%20were%20able%20to%20capitalize%20on%20this%20shift%20were%20the%20ones%20that%20executed%20on%20what%20I%20call%20the%20%26quot%3Bcity%20authentic%26quot%3B%20playbook.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20rise%20of%20influencer%20cities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20jobs%2C%20cities%20also%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20attract%20residents%20by%20being%2C%20well%2C%20attractive.%20At%20the%20turn%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bcity%20beautiful%26quot%3B%20movement%20launched%3A%20Governments%20and%20businesses%20built%20massive%2C%20ornate%20buildings%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20attract%20further%20investment.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20Washington%2C%20DC%20we%20know%20today%20%E2%80%94%20from%20the%20grand%20National%20Mall%20to%20the%20iconic%20neoclassical%20buildings%20%E2%80%94%20wasn't%20formally%20laid%20out%20until%201902%20as%20part%20of%20this%20movement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20such%20movement%20was%20the%20%26quot%3Bcity%20efficient%26quot%3B%20model%2C%20which%20leveraged%20Space%20Age%20technologies%20to%20modernize%20cities%20with%20precise%20engineering%20and%20strict%20use-based%20zoning%20laws.%20The%20national-highway%20system%20is%20perhaps%20the%20most%20transformative%20example%2C%20but%20this%20movement%20also%20gave%20us%20the%20modern%20steel-and-glass%20skyscraper.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20cities%20have%20turned%20to%20an%20economic%20development%20strategy%20I've%20deemed%20%26quot%3Bthe%20city%20authentic.%26quot%3B%20The%20new%20movement%20is%20largely%20predicated%20on%20nostalgia%20and%20the%20fetishization%20of%20%26quot%3Bthe%20local.%26quot%3B%20The%20pitch%20that%20cities%20using%20the%20%26quot%3Bcity%20authentic%26quot%3B%20playbook%20make%2C%20regardless%20of%20their%20particular%20amenities%2C%20is%20fairly%20similar%3A%20Their%20city%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bthrift-store%20find%2C%26quot%3B%20compared%20to%20the%20mainstream%20brand%20of%20major%20metropolises.%20They%20have%20old%20architecture%20that%20has%20been%20transformed%20into%20new%2C%20trendy%20offerings%20%E2%80%94%20all%20for%20a%20cheaper%20price.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThe%20aging%20buildings'%20authenticity%20reassures%20millennials%20that%20they%20are%20not%20living%20in%20their%20parents'%20cookie-cutter%20suburbs.%20They%20are%20experiencing%20something%20real.%20Their%20brunch%20means%20something.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20ad%20from%20the%20Fulton%20County%20Industrial%20Development%20Agency%2C%20or%20IDA%2C%20in%20upstate%20New%20York%20highlights%20its%20%26quot%3Bhistoric%2C%20grand%20buildings%20that%20feature%20distinctive%20architecture%2C%20100-year-old%20brick%2C%20and%20hardwood%20floors%2C%20surrounded%20by%20plentiful%20and%20free%20parking.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.southernliving.com%2Ftravel%2Fgeorgia%2Fathens-ga%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESouthern%20Living%20write%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20last%20year%2C%20Athens%2C%20Georgia%20%E2%80%94%20a%20town%20of%20120%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20boasts%20that%20%26quot%3Ban%20old%20tire%20company%20is%20now%20a%20favorite%20brewery%20and%20farmers'%20market.%20A%20kudzu-covered%20former%20cotton%20warehouse%20returns%20as%20an%20arts%20district%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F365publicationsonline.com%2FAthensNCG2021%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAthens%20Quality%20of%20Life%20Guide%3C%2Fa%3E%20emphasizes%20that%20median%20rents%20are%20%26quot%3B%24200%20less%20than%20the%20national%20average.%26quot%3B%20Tulsa%2C%20Oklahoma%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-pick-right-city-work-from-home-remote-employee-2022-6%5C%22%3Eoffered%20%2410%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20anyone%20who%20would%20move%20there%20for%20remote%20work%20%E2%80%94%20touting%20the%20city's%20%26quot%3Brevitalized%20Arts%20District%20that%20boasts%20hip%20coffee%20shops%2C%20vegan%20taco%20joints%2C%20steakhouse%20speakeasies%2C%20whiskey%20bars%2C%20art%20galleries%2C%20coworking%20spaces%2C%20and%20a%20software-development%20school.%26quot%3B%20In%20other%20words%2C%20these%20cities%20offer%20relative%20affordability%20without%20sacrificing%20the%20hip%20feel%20of%20an%20urban%20neighborhood.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20post-industrial%20economy%20such%20as%20ours%2C%20whether%20a%20city%20can%20attract%20new%20residents%20and%20investments%20can%20mean%20life%20or%20death%20for%20its%20local%20economy.%20But%20the%20challenge%20for%20cities%20following%20this%20playbook%20is%20balancing%20uniqueness%20and%20approachability.%20There%20is%20immense%20pressure%20to%2C%20paradoxically%2C%20fit%20in%20and%20stand%20out.%20Most%20square%20this%20circle%20with%20predictably%20unique%20cultural%20offerings%3A%20Craft%20breweries%20that%20offer%20the%20same%20litany%20of%20IPAs%20and%20lagers%2C%20but%20with%20each%20one%20named%20after%20something%20local%3B%20food%20halls%20with%20the%20same%20overpriced%20plates%20and%20decadent%20bloody%20marys%2C%20but%20everything%20is%20made%20locally%3B%20and%2C%20as%20Fulton%20county's%20IDA%20would%20like%20us%20to%20remember%2C%20it%20is%20all%20contained%20within%20beautiful%20brownstones%20and%20Victorians%20that%20were%20spared%20urban%20renewal's%20bulldozers.%20Years%20of%20neglect%20are%20turned%20into%20an%20asset%20because%20the%20aging%20buildings'%20authenticity%20reassures%20millennials%20that%20they%20are%20not%20living%20in%20their%20parents'%20cookie-cutter%20suburbs.%20They%20are%20experiencing%20something%20real.%20Their%20brunch%20means%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222553%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Industrial-looking%20Cafe%20Biaggio%20in%20St%20Paul%2C%20Minneapolis%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ba9222006a5e001949caa9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221915%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20industrial-looking%20restaurant%20could%20be%20found%20in%20almost%20any%20US%20city.%20This%20one%20is%20in%20Saint%20Paul%2C%20Minnesota.%3Cp%3EDAVID%20BREWSTER%2FStar%20Tribune%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20because%20so%20much%20of%20how%20we%20persuade%20and%20influence%20each%20other%20happens%20online%2C%20cities%20are%20increasingly%20making%20that%20case%20on%20social%20media%20with%20the%20help%20of%20influencers.%20Whether%20a%20dive%20bar%20or%20an%20entire%20neighborhood%20is%20perceived%20as%20unique%20and%20on-trend%20has%20a%20lot%20to%20do%20with%20how%20it%20circulates%20online.%20Social%20media%20and%20its%20attendant%20influencer%20industry%20have%20significantly%20changed%20how%20cities%20promote%20themselves.%20Ignoring%20the%20conflicting%20struggles%20that%20characterize%20the%20history%20of%20America's%20downtowns%2C%20the%20city%20authentic%20weathers%20that%20history%20down%20to%20a%20safe%2C%20entertaining%20story%20told%20through%20predictably%20unique%20experiences%2C%20menu%20items%2C%20and%20interior%20designs.%20All%20of%20which%20are%20meant%20to%20both%20stand%20out%20just%20enough%20to%20recognizably%20fit%20into%20the%20categories%2C%20genres%2C%20and%20vibes%20organized%20by%20social%20media's%20algorithms.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReal-estate%20agents%20now%20feel%20the%20pressure%20to%20up%20their%20Instagram%20game%20to%20promote%20not%20just%20their%20properties%2C%20but%20an%20entire%20market.%20It's%20considered%20a%20dereliction%20of%20duty%20if%20your%20downtown%20Business%20Improvement%20District%20doesn't%20have%20a%20social-media%20plan%20and%20someone%20to%20execute%20it.%20And%2C%20whether%20they're%20home-grown%20or%20hired%20from%20an%20agency%2C%20being%20featured%20on%20an%20influencer's%20account%20is%20a%20common%20tactic%20to%20raise%20a%20city's%20profile%20among%20young%20professionals.%20When%20the%20influencer%20chef%20Alison%20Roman%20needed%20to%20escape%20both%20COVID%20and%20a%20high-profile%20spat%20with%20Chrissy%20Teigen%2C%20she%20decamped%20for%20upstate%20New%20York%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F2021%2F12%2F20%2Falison-roman-just-cant-help-herself%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubsequent%20interviews%3C%2Fa%3E%20touted%20her%20investments%20in%20out-of-the-way%20Bloomsville%2C%20New%20York.%20Some%20influencers%20have%20even%20gone%20so%20far%20as%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thecut.com%2F2018%2F06%2Frookie-founder-tavi-gevinson-ends-sponsorship-with-apartment.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20their%20own%20apartment%3C%2Fa%3E%20sponsored%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETired%20replicas%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20is%20economic%20relief%20for%20those%20leaving%20the%20big%20cities%20for%20chic%20and%20affordable%20spots%2C%20it's%20not%20all%20ros%C3%A9%20brunches%20and%20glamping.%20There%20are%20real%20challenges%20and%20even%20a%20few%20dangers%20to%20using%20the%20%26quot%3Bcity%20authentic%26quot%3B%20playbook.%20As%20big-city%20high-earners%20move%20into%20town%2C%20landlords%20and%20restaurateurs%20immediately%20move%20to%20cater%20to%20them%2C%20raising%20prices%20and%20accommodating%20new%20tastes%2C%20which%20pushes%20out%20locals.%20As%20I%20demonstrate%20in%20my%20book%2C%20in%20upstate%20New%20York%2C%20Rensselaer%20county's%20population%20only%20went%20up%201%25%20between%202010%20and%202019%2C%20but%20median%20gross%20rent%20went%20up%2025%25%20over%20the%20same%20time%20span.%20It%20spiked%20even%20more%20during%20the%20pandemic%20when%20change%20of%20addresses%20from%20New%20York%20City%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesunion.com%2Fnews%2Farticle%2Fnew-york-city-residents-relocate-upstate-16070020.php%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejumped%20a%20whopping%20787%25%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20rent%20a%20one%20bedroom%20for%20%24600%20a%20month%20when%20I%20first%20moved%20to%20Troy%2C%20in%20Rensselaer%20County%2C%20in%202010.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20availability%20of%20housing%20in%20that%20price%20range%20has%20gone%20down%20by%2036%25.%20And%20this%20trend%20is%20happening%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fflagpole.com%2Fnews%2Fnews-features%2F2022%2F09%2F14%2Fwhy-rents-and-home-prices-have-gotten-so-high-in-athens%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eall%20across%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kjrh.com%2Fnews%2Flocal-news%2Fstudy-2-45-billion-needed-to-successfully-combat-tulsa-housing-crisis%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20threatening%20to%20make%20it%20impossible%20for%20essential%20workers%20like%20nurses%2C%20cooks%2C%20and%20teachers%20to%20live%20anywhere%20near%20where%20they%20work.%20The%20nine%20counties%20immediately%20north%20of%20New%20York%20City%20may%20have%20absorbed%20a%20lot%20of%20high-earning%20city%20folk%2C%20but%20even%20more%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pattern-for-progress.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2FPfP-Migration-Report-2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople%20left%20the%20region%3C%2Fa%3E%20due%20to%20rising%20prices%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20small%20net%20loss%20of%20population%20between%202019%20and%202020.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224594%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20on%20the%20deck%20of%20a%20brewery%20in%20Atlanta%2C%20Georgia%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ba917603c40c001a97ae03%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223435%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECraft%20breweries%20are%20popping%20up%20all%20across%20the%20US%20as%20part%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bcity%20authentic%26quot%3B%20playbook.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Greim%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20as%20the%20local%20haunts%20are%20replaced%20by%20Instagramable%20caf%C3%A9s%20and%20art%20galleries%2C%20the%20city%20feels%20less%20like%20home%20and%20more%20like%20someone%20else's%20lifestyle%20brand.%20The%20pressures%20to%20be%20predictably%20unique%20can%20suffocate%20the%20distinctive%20identity%20that%20begat%20a%20region's%20success%20in%20the%20first%20place%20%E2%80%94%20turning%20cities%20into%20tired%20replicas%20of%20each%20other.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20none%20of%20this%20guarantees%20financial%20success%2C%20either.%20City%20governments%2C%20eager%20to%20win%20the%20all-against-all%20fight%20for%20capital%20investment%2C%20are%20happy%20to%20offer%20tax-break%20enticements%20to%20developers.%20So%20while%20construction%20cranes%20may%20signal%20economic%20success%20and%20there%20may%20be%20an%20influx%20of%20cash%20from%20building%20permitting%20and%20new%20residents'%20spending%2C%20cities%20will%20eventually%20find%20that%20there's%20no%20money%20to%20repair%20the%20roads%20and%20pipes%20that%20lead%20to%20all%20this%20new%20development.%20All%20the%20emergency%20calls%20and%20trash%20these%20new%20apartment%20buildings%20generate%20need%20to%20be%20dealt%20with%20too%2C%20and%20that%20costs%20money.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20worth%20saying%20that%20there%20is%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20enjoying%20your%20weekend%20farmers-market%20jaunt%20(I%20know%20I%20do).%20Making%20a%20city%20that's%20exciting%2C%20fun%2C%20and%20inviting%20is%20an%20unalloyed%20good%20thing.%20But%20the%20default%20way%20cities%20do%20it%20now%20is%20creating%20unaffordable%20and%20uninspired%20cityscapes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20avoid%20these%20challenges%2C%20some%20cutting-edge%20cities%20have%20gotten%20creative.%20Newark%2C%20New%20Jersey%20set%20up%20a%20revolving%20loan%20fund%20to%20convert%20privately%20held%20small%20businesses%20into%20Employee%20Stock%20Ownership%20Plans%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanprogress.org%2Farticle%2Fbuilding-workers-wealth-cities-states%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20recognized%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20great%20way%20to%20keep%20money%20in%20a%20community%20after%20a%20business%20owner%20retires.%20Other%20cities%20could%20reverse%20a%20trend%20that%20began%20in%20the%2060s%20where%20satelite%20communities%20and%20suburbs%20formed%20their%20own%20(usually%20whiter%20and%20wealthier)%20municipal%20governments%2C%20splitting%20city%20resources.%20Reconsolidating%20cities%20would%20reduce%20overhead%20costs%20of%20running%20them%20and%20increase%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20essentials%3A%20water%2C%20public%20safety%2C%20and%20waste%20disposal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHousing%20is%20also%20a%20crucial%20piece%20of%20the%20puzzle.%20While%20some%20cities%20definitely%20need%20to%20increase%20supply%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffurmancenter.org%2Fthestoop%2Fentry%2Fsupply-skepticism-housing-supply-and-affordability%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20suggests%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20this%20%26quot%3Bwill%20never%20supply%20adequate%20housing%20for%20low-%20and%20moderate-income%20households.%26quot%3B%20Rent%20control%20and%20public%20housing%20are%20important%20tools%20here%2C%20but%20another%20option%20that%20may%20be%20less%20politically%20contentious%20is%20the%20formation%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bostonreview.net%2Farticles%2Fa-path-to-neighborhood-power%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eneighborhood%20trust%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Unlike%20renting%2C%20neighborhood%20trusts%20like%20the%20Dudley%20Street%20Neighborhood%20Initiative%20in%20Boston%20allows%20residents%20to%20manage%20permanently%20affordable%20housing%20on%20their%20own%20terms%20while%20also%20building%20up%20a%20bit%20of%20equity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20their%20approach%2C%20cities%20that%20have%20borne%20the%20brunt%20of%20the%20large-city%20exodus%20will%20need%20to%20manage%20their%20sought-after%20growth%20sustainably.%20If%20they%20don't%2C%20the%20hype%20of%20America's%20new%20Generic%20Towns%20is%20certain%20to%20fade.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fdavid-a-banks%5C%22%3EDavid%20A.%20Banks%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20lecturer%20and%20Director%20of%20Globalization%20Studies%20at%20University%20at%20Albany%20SUNY.%20He%20is%20also%20the%2