%3ETraditionally%2C%20Israel%E2%80%99s%C2%A0Supreme%20Court%20has%20had%20a%20relatively%20strong%20position%20as%20there%20is%20no%20second%20chamber%20in%20parliament%20that%20can%20keep%C2%A0Knesset%C2%A0legislation%20in%20check.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20focus%20right%20now%20is%20on%20the%20so-called%20adequacy%20clause%3A%20until%20now%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20been%20able%20to%20declare%20government%20decisions%20as%20%E2%80%9Cinappropriate%E2%80%9D%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20make%20them%20null%20and%20void.%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20government%20wanted%20to%20put%20an%20end%20to%20this%20clause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20first%20vote%20in%20mid-July%2C%20the%20decisive%20vote%20was%20on%20Monday.%20Out%20of%20a%20total%20of%20120%20Knesset%20members%2C%20all%2064%20government%20MPs%20voted%20yes%2C%20which%20means%20the%20law%20has%20now%20been%20passed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20step%20of%20the%20judicial%20reform%20is%20due%20to%20be%20voted%20on%20in%20the%20Knesset%20as%20early%20as%20autumn%3A%20if%20passed%2C%20it%20would%C2%A0give%20the%20government%20more%20powers%20over%20judicial%20appointments.%C2%A0Over%20recent%20months%2C%20however%2C%20Netanyahu%20has%20indicated%20that%20he%20might%20be%20willing%20to%20partially%20concede%C2%A0in%20this%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20those%20in%20favour%20argue%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20the%20120%20members%20of%20the%20Knesset%2C%20judges%20are%20not%20directly%20elected%20by%20the%20people.%20That%20is%20why%20the%20government%20and%20its%20supporters%20argue%20that%20their%20proposed%20judicial%20reform%20would%20strengthen%20Israeli%20democracy.%20From%20their%20point%20of%20view%2C%20the%20judiciary%20has%20too%20much%20power%C2%A0and%20the%20proposed%20reform%C2%A0would%20in%20fact%20improve%20the%20balance%20between%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20supporters%20of%20the%20reform%20have%20also%20taken%20to%20the%20streets%20for%20counter-protests.%20According%20to%20media%20reports%2C%20around%2050%2C000%20participants%20were%20counted%20in%20Tel%20Aviv%20on%20Sunday%20evening%2C%20including%20many%20residents%20from%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20country%20and%20settlers%20from%20the%20Israeli-occupied%20West%20Bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25125403%2FNetanyahu-1024x683.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22690%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25125403%2FNetanyahu-1024x683.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25125403%2FNetanyahu-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25125403%2FNetanyahu.jpg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664935%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22460%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBenjamin%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20government%20is%20seen%20as%20very%20conservative%20and%20nationalist.%20Photo%3A%20Av%20Jolanda%20Flubacher%2FWorld%20Economic%20Forum%2Fswiss-image.ch.%20CC%20BY-SA%202.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judicial%20reform%20is%20being%20pushed%20primarily%20by%20nationalist%20and%20religious%20parties%20in%20the%20governing%20coalition.%20The%20far-right%20minister%20for%20national%20security%2C%20Itamar%20Ben-Gvir%2C%20recently%20declared%20that%20his%20party%20%E2%80%98Jewish%20Strength%E2%80%99%20would%20reject%20%E2%80%9Cany%20softening%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20draft%20law%20as%20%E2%80%9Ccastration%E2%80%9D.%20He%20called%20on%20the%20coalition%20to%20pass%20the%20law%20in%20its%20current%20form%20and%20to%20move%20forward%20with%20the%20next%20parts%20of%20the%20reform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20criticism%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20critics%20of%20the%20reform%2C%20however%2C%20the%20government%20is%20planning%20nothing%20less%20than%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdestruction%20of%20democracy%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20a%20slogan%20on%20many%20posters%20and%20banners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProtesters%20have%20also%20drawn%20comparisons%20with%20Poland%20and%20Hungary%2C%20whose%20respective%20governments%20are%20also%20accused%20of%20trying%20to%20restructure%20the%20judiciary.%20The%20two%20countries%20are%20often%20considered%20problematic%20in%20the%20European%20Union%20with%20regard%20to%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20separation%20of%20powers%2C%20and%20both%20are%20facing%20several%20infringement%20procedures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECritics%20argue%20that%20judicial%20reform%20in%20Israel%20could%20cause%20a%20deeper%20division%20of%20society%3A%20in%20the%20past%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20repeatedly%20defended%20values%20such%20as%20gender%20equality%20and%20the%20protection%20of%20sexual%20minorities%20against%20strict%20religious%20restrictions.%20Many%20Israelis%20who%20consider%20themselves%20as%20secular%2C%20left-wing%20or%20liberal%20fear%20the%20restructuring%20would%20strengthen%20the%20ultra-Orthodox%20wing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20has%20even%20reached%20the%20army%2C%20where%20mandatory%20service%20for%20men%20and%20women%20is%20seen%20as%20promoting%20a%20melting%20pot%20and%20acting%20as%20a%20social%20glue.%20Ultra-Orthodox%20Jews%20are%20exempt%20from%20this%20service%2C%20which%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20repeatedly%20declared%20discriminatory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20weekend%2C%20more%20than%201%2C000%20Israeli%20Air%20Force%20reservists%20threatened%20to%20quit%20their%20voluntary%20service%20if%20the%20judicial%20reform%20were%20passed.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20all%20have%20a%20collective%20responsibility%20for%20overcoming%20deep%20divisions%2C%20polarization%20and%20rifts%20among%20the%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20said%20in%20a%20joint%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20was%20also%20boosted%20by%20support%20from%20members%20of%20numerous%20other%20units%2C%20including%20reservists%20from%20the%20domestic%20and%20foreign%20intelligence%20services%20Shin%20Bet%20and%20Mossad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20next%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAuthorities%20are%20preparing%20for%20more%20angry%20protests%3A%20according%20to%20the%20police%2C%20officers%20were%20preparing%20in%20case%20they%20had%20to%20prevent%20protesters%20from%20entering%20the%20Knesset.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECivil%20society%20groups%20such%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9CMovement%20for%20Quality%20Government%E2%80%9D%20said%20right%20after%20the%20vote%20that%20they%20would%20take%20the%20revised%20adequacy%20clause%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Judges%20will%20then%20have%20to%20check%20whether%20their%20own%20partial%20disempowerment%20would%20be%20constitutional.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20they%20were%20to%20block%20the%20reform%2C%20Israel%20would%20probably%20find%20itself%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20a%20national%20crisis.%20To%20avert%20this%2C%20the%20government%20would%20likely%20have%20to%20withdraw%20the%20reform%20%E2%80%93%20a%20scenario%20that%20many%20observers%20expect%20would%20lead%20to%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20coalition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fisraels-judicial-reform-and-what-it-means-for-the-country%2Fa-66332764%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690270784000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25124531%2FIsrael-judicial-reform-protests-II.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwith-israel-knesset-focused-on-reforms-what-is-at-stake%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22