and%20the%20film%20is%20expected%20to%20go%20on%20floors%20next%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fveere-di-wedding-2-will-happen-the-film-is-expected-to-go-on-floors-next-year%2Farticleshow%2F102100922.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20FY23%2C%20LPG%20Refills%20Under%20Ujjwala%20Fell%2C%2012%25%20Of%20Beneficiaries%20Didn%E2%80%99t%20Get%20a%20Single%20Refill%3A%20Govt%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F03%2F26113648%2F2020_3img25_Mar_2020_PTI25-03-2020_000080B.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20After%20witnessing%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20number%20of%20subsidised%20LPG%20refills%20in%20the%20financial%20year%202020-21%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Ujjwala%20Yojana%20(PMUY)%2C%20the%20trend%20has%20shown%20a%20decline%20in%20FY23.%20The%20average%20number%20of%20refills%20per%20year%20has%20declined%20to%203.7%2C%20down%20from%204.4%20in%20FY21.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.financialexpress.com%2Feconomy%2Fujjwala-scheme-lpg-bottle-refills-remain-low%2F3185193%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20FY19%20and%20FY20%2C%20the%20average%20number%20of%20LPG%20refills%20per%20year%20was%20three%20bottles%2C%20which%20rose%20to%204.4%20bottles%20in%20FY21.%20In%20the%20subsequent%20two%20years%2C%20it%20dropped%20to%20around%203.7%20refills%20per%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20noted%20that%20this%20decrease%20reflects%20the%20stagnant%20income%20levels%20among%20the%20beneficiaries.%20However%2C%20it%20added%20that%20some%20smaller%20households%20may%20not%20require%20more%20than%20four%20refills%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20the%2095.9%20million%20PMUY%20beneficiaries%2C%2011.8%20million%20(about%2012%25)%20did%20not%20get%20even%20a%20single%20LPG%20bottle%20during%20the%20last%20financial%20year%2C%20said%20minister%20of%20state%20of%20petroleum%20and%20natural%20gas%2C%20Rameswar%20Teli%2C%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20some%20beneficiaries%20used%20less%20than%20four%20bottles%20of%20cooking%20fuel%20during%20the%20year%20despite%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20subsidy%20of%20Rs%20200%20per%20bottle%20for%20up%20to%2012%20bottles%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20April%202023%2C%20the%20price%20of%20an%20unsubsidised%20domestic%20LPG%20bottle%20(14.2%20kg)%20in%20Delhi%20stood%20at%20Rs%201%2C103.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20July%201%2C%202023%2C%20there%20were%20approximately%2095.9%20million%20PMUY%20beneficiaries%2C%20out%20of%20which%2084.1%20million%20had%20taken%20at%20least%20one%20refill%20during%20the%202022-23%20period%2C%20said%20Teli.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%201%2C%202022%2C%20Teli%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fnews%2Fenergy%2Fujjwala-over-9-million-beneficiaries-did-not-refill-cylinder-last-year-centre-admits-84130%5C%22%3Ehad%20told%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20that%209.2%20million%20customers%20did%20not%20take%20any%20refill%20in%202021-22.%20The%20Union%20government%20had%20admitted%20that%20the%20PMUY%20beneficiaries%20had%20not%20been%20able%20to%20fill%20cylinders%20due%20to%20high%20prices%20of%20LPG.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELaunched%20in%202016%2C%20PMUY%20aims%20to%20provide%20deposit-free%20LPG%20connections%20to%20adult%20women%20from%20poor%20households%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20target%20of%20releasing%2080%20million%20connections%20was%20achieved%20in%202019%2C%20and%20the%20second%20phase%2C%20Ujjwala%202.0%2C%20added%2016%20million%20additional%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20Census%202011%2C%20there%20are%20315%20million%20domestic%20LPG%20consumers%20in%20India%2C%20covering%20105.1%25%20of%20estimated%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20promote%20the%20use%20of%20LPG%2C%20the%20government%20has%20implemented%20various%20measures%2C%20including%20subsidies%20that%20were%20extended%20for%20a%20year%20last%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20updated%20household%20numbers%20are%20not%20available%2C%20as%20the%20Census%202021%20has%20not%20been%20conducted%2C%20reported%20the%20ministry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20imports%20over%2060%25%20of%20its%20domestic%20LPG%20consumption%2C%20and%20from%202020-21%20to%202022-23%2C%20the%20average%20Saudi%20CP%20(international%20benchmark%20for%20LPG%20pricing)%20increased%20from%20%24415%20per%20million%20tonne%20(MT)%20to%20%24712%20per%20MT.%20However%2C%20the%20full%20increase%20in%20international%20prices%20was%20not%20passed%20on%20to%20Indian%20citizens%2C%20resulting%20in%20public%20sector%20oil%20marketing%20companies%20suffering%20under%20recoveries%20of%20about%20Rs%2028%2C000%20crore%20on%20the%20sale%20of%20domestic%20LPG.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20compensate%20for%20this%2C%20the%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Fenergy%2Foil-gas%2Fcentre-announces-one-time-compensation-of-rs-22000-crore-for-omcs-to-recover-lpg-losses%2Farticleshow%2F94810537.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Eapproved%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20one-time%20compensation%20of%20Rs%2022%2C000%20crore%20to%20OMCs%20in%20FY23.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20subsidy%20for%20domestic%20LPG%20connections%20decreased%20from%20Rs%2037%2C209%20crore%20in%202018-19%20to%20Rs%206%2C965%20crore%20in%20FY23.%20This%20subsidy%20amount%20includes%20the%20expenditure%20on%20connections%20provided%20under%20PMUY%2C%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690269662000%2C%