resses%20and%20the%20anguish%20of%20her%20primary%20character%2C%20Rachel%20Vinrace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Woolf%20and%20her%20chief%20protagonist%20had%20domineering%20father%20figures%2C%20had%20lost%20their%20mothers%20at%20a%20relatively%20young%20age%2C%20and%20were%20denied%20a%20formal%20education%20%E2%80%93%20instead%20being%20schooled%20at%20home.%20Laying%20out%20her%20character%E2%80%99s%20mental%20life%20so%20starkly%20caused%20Woolf%20some%20discomfort.%20A%20new%20edition%20may%20have%20provided%20an%20opportunity%20to%20reconsider.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20plausible%20theory.%20But%20does%20the%20evidence%20in%20Woolf%E2%80%99s%20corrections%20bear%20it%20out%3F%20There%20are%20two%20main%20places%20in%20the%20text%20where%20the%20majority%20of%20changes%20are%20indicated%3A%20both%20are%20pivotal%20moments%20in%20the%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20set%20of%20changes%20occurs%20in%20Chapter%20XVI%2C%20where%20the%20conversation%20between%20Vinrace%20and%20Terence%20Hewet%20%E2%80%93%20the%20pair%20occupying%20the%20romantic%20plotline%20of%20the%20novel%20%E2%80%93%20is%20altered%20to%20reduce%20access%20to%20Rachel%E2%80%99s%20inner%20thoughts.%20Entire%20paragraphs%20are%20replaced%20by%20typed%20text%20pasted%20directly%20onto%20the%20page%2C%20where%20the%20narrator%20studies%20Rachel%20without%20the%20guarantee%20of%20understanding%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20the%20effect%20of%20diluting%20some%20uncomfortable%20autobiographical%20elements%20in%20the%20text%2C%20but%20also%20marks%20a%20significant%20shift%20in%20the%20way%20narration%20accesses%20the%20minds%20of%20characters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20narrator%20is%20bounded%20by%20the%20limits%20of%20character%20itself%3A%20the%20depths%20of%20Rachel%E2%80%99s%20subjectivity%20are%20unknown%20even%20to%20her.%20This%20bears%20the%20mark%20of%20modern%20psychology%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fa-dangerous-method-in-defence-of-freuds-psychoanalysis-5989%5C%22%3EFreud%E2%80%99s%20theory%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20unconscious%2C%20in%20the%20years%20before%20and%20during%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20novel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Freally-believe-everything-say%5C%22%3EDo%20We%20Really%20Believe%20in%20Everything%20We%20Say%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20modernist%20revolution%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20innovation%20signals%20a%20profound%20shift%20in%20modernist%20fiction%2C%20which%20began%20in%20the%20late%2019th%20and%20early%2020th%20centuries%20and%20is%20characterised%20by%20a%20self-conscious%20break%20with%20traditional%20ways%20of%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20240px)%2085vw%2C%20240px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25115913%2FThe-Voyage-Out-194x300.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22240%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25115913%2FThe-Voyage-Out-194x300.jpg%20194w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25115913%2FThe-Voyage-Out-662x1024.jpg%20662w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25115913%2FThe-Voyage-Out.jpg%20753w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664901%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22371%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EVirginia%20Woolf%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Voyage%20Out%3C%2Fem%3E%20Penguin%20Classics%20(2006)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20unknowability%20of%20Woolf%E2%80%99s%20characters%20begins%20with%20the%20dark%20regions%20of%20the%20mind.%20No%20longer%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20realism%2C%20where%20thoughts%20and%20actions%20are%20knowable%20(and%20often%20transmitted%20by%20an%20omniscient%20narrator)%2C%20instead%20the%20narrator%20provides%20a%20portrait%20of